<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Martinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obovata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="21">Martinella obovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed geographically through an area that is â‰¥ 2000 km2, with &lt;20% of its known individuals occurring outside Protected Areas, and seventy-two 
<bibRefCitation author="Rapoport, EH" journalOrPublisher="Pergamon, New York, USA" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refId="B15" refString="Rapoport, EH, 1982. Aerography: Geographical Strategies of Species. Pergamon, New York, USA" title="Aerography: Geographical Strategies of Species" year="1982">Rapoport (1982)</bibRefCitation>
sub-populations known to date. Therefore, this species is here considered as Least Concern [LC] according to the IUCN criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK" pageId="7" pageNumber="22" refId="B6" refString="IUCN, , 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
